Here's the adapted version of the `open-lovable` project based on your instructions. I'll provide a modified `README.md` and a new implementation structure:

## Modified README.md

```markdown
# Open-Lovable Enhanced

A modernized version of open-lovable with additional features for website cloning and transformation.

## Features

1. **Website Cloning Engine**:
   - Primary: [goclone](https://github.com/goclone-dev/goclone.git)
   - Fallback: [webpage2html](https://github.com/zTrix/webpage2html.git)

2. **Site Transformation**:
   - HTML code analysis and modernization
   - User-specified changes via UI or file upload
   - Persistent chat interface for iterative improvements

3. **Enhanced LLM Integration**:
   - New endpoint: Helmholtz Code Model
   - Aliases:
     - `alias-large`: For planning tasks
     - `alias-huge`: For full codebase context queries

4. **Robust Error Handling**:
   - 501 error recovery with exponential backoff (30s → 60s after 5 attempts)

## Implementation Structure

```
open-lovable/
├── core/                  # Core functionality
│   ├── clone/             # Website cloning components
│   │   ├── goclone/       # Primary cloning engine
│   │   └── webpage2html/  # Fallback cloning engine
│   ├── transform/         # Site transformation logic
│   └── chat/              # Chat interface
├── api/                   # API endpoints
│   ├── url-endpoint/      # URL processing endpoint
│   └── llm-endpoint/      # LLM integration
└── error-handling/        # Robust error recovery
```

## Setup Instructions

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/JsonLord/open-lovable.git
cd open-lovable
```

2. Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install
# or
yarn install
```

3. Configure the cloning engines:
```bash
# For goclone
git clone https://github.com/goclone-dev/goclone.git core/clone/goclone

# For webpage2html fallback
git clone https://github.com/zTrix/webpage2html.git core/clone/webpage2html
```

4. Build and run:
```bash
npm run build
npm start
```

## API Endpoints

### URL Processing
- `POST /api/clone` - Accepts URL to clone and transform
- Request body: `{ "url": "https://example.com" }`

### LLM Integration
- `POST /api/llm` - Query the Helmholtz model
- Request body: `{ "query": "your question", "alias": "alias-large|alias-huge" }`

## Error Handling

The system implements intelligent retry logic for 501 errors:
1. First 5 attempts: 30-second delay between retries
2. Subsequent attempts: 60-second delay

## Contributing

